external_knowledge:
- 'create' permission indicates the ability to create content;
- The hierarchy is built based on the parent-child relationship in the content table;
- The level indicates the depth of the content item in the hierarchy.

- "Blossoms" refers to content items;
- "Live" means the content items are active and not archived;
- "Visible in the menu" means the content items are marked to be shown in menus;
- "More than one translation" means the content items have more than one associated translation record.

- 'Admins' is a user group with administrative privileges;
- 'live' indicates that the content item is currently active or visible;
- 'translations' refer to localized versions of the content.

- 'live' content refers to content that is currently active and visible to users;
- 'show_in_menus' indicates that the content is included in navigation menus;
- 'created_at' is the timestamp when the content was first created.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(id) AS active_user_groups_count
FROM user_groups
WHERE is_active = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "drafts of content items" refers to content items that are not live and have unpublished changes;
- "sitting idly" implies content types that do not have any permissions associated with them;
- "permissions granted" refers to the existence of at least one permission for the content type.

- "Top level" refers to content items with a depth of 1 in the content hierarchy;
- "Live content items" are those where the `live` column is set to 1;
- "Latest published revision" refers to the highest revision number where the status is 'published'.

- 'Page' refers to a specific type of content identified by the `slug` in the `content_types` table;
- 'Translation' refers to a content revision with a different language or version;
- 'Published' indicates that a translation has been made public and is visible to users.

