external_knowledge:
- "Flowers have bloomed" refers to content items that are marked as live (published);
- "Types of flowers" refers to content types;
- "Blossoms" refer to the number of published content items for each content type.

- 'Seeds' metaphorically represent content items;
- 'Garden of blog posts' refers to the content type 'blog-post';
- 'Planting new saplings' represents the 'create' permission.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.content_type_id) AS unique_content_types
FROM content c
JOIN content_type_permissions cp ON c.content_type_id = cp.content_type_id;
